      "description": "Taxes the transfer of a taxable estate located in Hawaii by a nonresident who is not a citizen of the United States. Specifies that a decedent shall be entitled to all applicable exclusion or exemption amounts as determined under the Internal Revenue Code as of December 31, 2009, before being subject to any taxes, including up to a $3,500,000 applicable exclusion amount. Amends the definition of \"Internal Revenue Code\" to include certain federal tax principles. Adds definitions of \"nonresident not a citizen\" and \"noncitizen transfer\". Retains the State's ability to \"pick-up\" the state death tax credit as it existed in the Internal Revenue Code on December 31, 2000. (HB2866 CD1)"
